title: Pasta with garlic and parmesan
recipe: ['Cook pasta according to package directions.', 'Drain and set aside.', 'In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.', 'Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.', 'Add butter and cook for 1 minute.', 'Add salt and pepper.', 'Add pasta and toss to coat.', 'Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and serve.']

title: Bbq chicken wings
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Mix barbecue sauce and pepper.', 'Reserve 1/4 cup barbecue sauce mixture.', 'Grill chicken 15 min.', 'Or until done, turning and brushing occasionally with remaining barbecue sauce mixture.']

title: Chocolate brownies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Line 8-inch square baking pan with foil, with ends of foil extending over sides.', 'Spray with cooking spray.', 'Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Blend in eggs and vanilla.', 'Add flour, cocoa powder and baking powder; mix well.', 'Spread into prepared pan.', 'Bake 25 to 30 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.', '(do not overbake.)', 'Cool completely.', 'Use foil handles to lift brownies from pan before cutting into bars.']

title: Sparkling pomegranate limeade
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a pitcher.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Orange flan
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Place sugar in small saucepan; cook on medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.', 'Add water; cook until mixture comes to boil.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, stirring with wire whisk until well blended after each addition.', 'Pour into 9-inch round pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until center is almost set.', 'Run knife around rim of pan to loosen flan; cool before removing rim.', 'Refrigerate 4 hours.', 'Meanwhile, bring water to boil in medium saucepan.', 'Add sugar; stir until dissolved.', 'Add oranges; cook on medium-low heat 5 min.', 'Or until oranges are tender, stirring occasionally.', 'Remove']

title: Grilled chicken wings
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium heat.', 'Mix first 4 ingredients until blended.', 'Reserve 1/4 cup dressing mixture; brush remaining onto chicken.', 'Grill 15 min.', 'Or until done, turning occasionally.', 'Brush with reserved dressing mixture.']

title: Fried bread with cinnamon butter
recipe: ['In a large bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, cinnamon and salt.', 'Add the bread and toss to coat.', 'Let stand for 10 minutes.', 'In a large skillet, heat the oil.', 'Add the bread and cook over moderate heat, turning once, until golden and crisp, about 4 minutes.', 'Transfer the bread to paper towels to drain.', 'Serve hot.']

title: Salmon with dill
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Place salmon fillets in a baking dish.', 'Sprinkle dill, salt, and pepper over salmon.', 'Bake in preheated oven until salmon flakes easily with a fork, about 15 minutes.']

title: Chocolate chunk blondies
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Line 13x9-inch pan with foil, with ends of foil extending over sides.', 'Spray with cooking spray.', 'Microwave unsweetened chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Blend in eggs and vanilla.', 'Add flour and salt; mix well.', 'Stir in chopped chocolate.', 'Spread into prepared pan.', 'Bake 25 to 30 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.', '(do not overbake.)', 'Cool completely.', 'Use foil handles to lift dessert from pan before cutting into bars.']

title: Chicken parmesan
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Mix dressing and garlic until blended.', 'Place chicken in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray; drizzle with dressing mixture.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until chicken is done (165 degrees f).', 'Top with cheese; bake 5 min.', 'Or until melted.']

title: Grilled vegetables
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Toss vegetables with dressing; place in shallow dish.', 'Refrigerate 30 min.', 'To marinate.', 'Remove vegetables from marinade; discard marinade.', 'Grill vegetables 10 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender, turning occasionally.']

title: Triple-layer chocolate pie
recipe: ['Beat pudding mixes and milk with whisk 2 min.', '; pour into crust.', 'Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.', 'Top with cool whip just before serving.']

title: Scrambled eggs with milk
recipe: ['In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, salt and pepper.', 'Melt the butter in a large nonstick skillet.', 'Add the eggs and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the eggs are set but still moist, about 2 minutes.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Shrimp and pineapple ceviche
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the shrimp, pineapple, onion, cilantro, garlic, lime juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.', 'Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.', 'Serve with tortilla chips.']

title: Aperol spritz
recipe: ['In a pitcher, combine the aperol, prosecco, orange juice, and bitters.', 'Pour into ice-filled wineglasses and garnish with the orange slices.']

title: Cheesy salsa dip
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients until well blended; cover.', 'Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.', 'Serve with assorted cut-up fresh vegetables.']

title: Cheesy beef and tomato casserole
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Brown meat in large skillet; drain.', 'Stir in tomatoes, water, onion, salt and pepper.', 'Bring to boil.', 'Stir in macaroni; cover.', 'Simmer on medium-low heat 10 min.', 'Or until macaroni is tender.', 'Stir in cheese sauce mix until blended.', 'Spoon into 2-qt.', 'Casserole sprayed with cooking spray; top with shredded cheese.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until heated through.']

title: Tequila limeade
recipe: ['In a pitcher, combine the tequila, lime juice, sugar and water.', 'Stir until the sugar dissolves.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Brussels sprouts with parmesan
recipe: ['Cook brussels sprouts in boiling water in large saucepan 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender; drain.', 'Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add cheese; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or until melted.', 'Stir in sprouts; cook 2 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.']

title: Parmesan croutons
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.', 'Toss with olive oil and salt and pepper.', 'Spread on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes, tossing once or twice.', 'Remove from oven and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.', 'Return to oven and bake for another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.']

title: Poppy seed scones
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.', 'Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'In a small bowl, combine egg, milk and poppy seeds.', 'Add to flour mixture and stir just until moistened.', 'Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently for about 10 seconds.', 'Pat dough into a circle about 1/2 inch thick.', 'Cut into wedges.', 'Place wedges on a greased baking sheet.', 'Brush tops with egg wash.', 'Bake for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.']

title: Almond streusel coffee cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease and flour a 9x13 inch pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the almond extract.', 'Combine the flour, salt and cinnamon; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.', 'Spread batter into the prepared pan.', 'In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, flour and cinnamon; sprinkle over the batter.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.']

title: Cinnamon pancakes
recipe: ['Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.', 'Whisk eggs, milk and oil in medium bowl until blended.', 'Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.', '(batter will be lumpy.)', 'Heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat.', 'Ladle batter into skillet, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.', 'Cook until bubbles form on tops, then turn to brown other sides.', 'Serve topped with butter and syrup.']

title: Chocolate peanut butter marshmallow squares
recipe: ['Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Stir in marshmallows.', 'Spread onto bottom of foil-lined 8-inch square pan.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.', 'Cut into 24 squares to serve.']

title: Chocolate marshmallow squares
recipe: ['Microwave butter and chocolate in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Add marshmallow creme; mix well.', 'Press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Microwave marshmallow creme and milk in microwaveable bowl on high 1-1/2 min.', 'Or until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is well blended, stirring after each minute.', 'Pour over crust.', 'Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.', 'Cut into squares to serve.']

title: Jell-o pudding
recipe: ['Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.', 'Stir in milk.', 'Pour into a bowl and refrigerate until set.']

title: Cinnamon sugar cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the egg and vanilla.', 'Combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; stir into the creamed mixture.', 'Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on a greased baking sheet.', 'Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.', 'Remove from the oven and let cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Spaghetti with sun-dried tomatoes and garlic
recipe: ['Cook pasta according to package directions.', 'Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.', 'Add tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes begin to break down, about 5 minutes.', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.', 'Drain pasta and toss with tomato mixture.', 'Sprinkle with cheese and serve.']

title: Tomato & feta salad
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.']

title: Grilled corn with cilantro lime
recipe: ['Preheat grill to medium-high heat.', 'In a small bowl, combine the lime zest, garlic, cumin, salt and pepper.', 'Brush the corn with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper.', 'Grill the corn until tender, about 5 minutes per side.', 'Transfer to a platter and drizzle with the lime juice.', 'Sprinkle with cilantro and serve.']

title: Cinnamon muffins
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400f.', 'Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.', 'Whisk egg, milk and oil in medium bowl until blended.', 'Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.', '(batter will be lumpy.)', 'Stir in cinnamon.', 'Spoon into 12 greased or paper-lined medium muffin cups.', 'Bake 20 to 25 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in centres comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan 5 min.', 'Remove to wire racks; cool completely.']

title: Bbq chicken breasts
recipe: ['Heat oven to 375f.', 'Place chicken in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Mix barbecue sauce and sugar; pour over chicken.', 'Bake 30 min.', 'Or until chicken is done (165 degrees f).']

title: Garlic-shrimp linguine
recipe: ['Cook spaghetti as directed on package, omitting salt.', 'Meanwhile, heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium-high heat.', 'Add shrimp; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until shrimp turn pink.', 'Stir in garlic; cook 1 min.', 'Add spaghetti sauce and parsley; cook 2 to 3 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Drain spaghetti; place in large bowl.', 'Add shrimp mixture; toss to coat.']

title: Cheesy onion casserole
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.', 'Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat; cook and stir onion in melted butter until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir onion into onion; cook and stir until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir cheddar cheese, cheddar cheese, milk, salt, and black pepper into onion mixture; pour into prepared casserole dish.', 'Bake in preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.']

title: Roasted brussels sprouts with garlic
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, toss brussels sprouts with olive oil, salt, and pepper.', 'Spread in a single layer on a baking sheet.', 'Roast for 20 minutes, tossing halfway through.', 'Remove from oven and toss with garlic and butter.', 'Return to oven and roast for another 10 minutes, stirring once.']

title: Orange iced tea
recipe: ['In a large saucepan, bring water to a boil.', 'Add tea bags and steep for 5 minutes.', 'Remove tea bags and add sugar.', 'Stir until sugar is dissolved.', 'Add orange slices and lemon slices.', 'Chill until cold.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Orange iced tea
recipe: ['Place drink mix in large plastic or glass pitcher.', 'Add water; stir until drink mix is dissolved.', 'Stir in orange juice.', 'Serve over ice cubes in tall glasses.']

title: Cabbage slaw
recipe: ['Combine cabbage, onions and peppers in large bowl.', 'Mix remaining ingredients until blended.', 'Add to cabbage mixture; toss to coat.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.']

title: Cinnamon streusel coffee cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.', 'In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.', 'Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'In a small bowl, combine egg, milk and 1 tablespoon of the cinnamon.', 'Add to flour mixture and stir just until moistened.', 'Pour batter into prepared pan.', 'In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and remaining cinnamon.', 'Sprinkle over batter.', 'Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.']

title: Scalloped potatoes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.', 'In a large bowl, combine the potatoes, sour cream, milk, onion, salt and pepper.', 'Mix well and pour into the prepared baking dish.', 'In a small bowl, combine the melted butter and parmesan cheese.', 'Sprinkle over the potatoes.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour, or until potatoes are tender.']

title: Peanut butter cupcakes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. line a 12-cup muffin tin with paper liners.', 'In a large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together peanut butter, oil, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla until smooth.', 'Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and stir until just combined.', 'Divide batter among muffin cups.', 'Bake for 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a cupcake comes out clean.', 'Cool in the pan for 5 minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Cinnamon biscuits
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 450 degrees f (230 degrees c).', 'In a medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.', 'Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in milk just until dough forms.', 'Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.', 'Knead lightly 4 to 5 times.', 'Roll dough out to 1/4 inch thickness.', 'Cut with a biscuit cutter.', 'Place biscuits 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.']

title: Banana crunch
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.', 'In a large bowl, combine the bananas, sugar and butter.', 'Mix well and spread into the prepared baking dish.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.']

title: Chicken with garlic and peppers
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chicken; cook 5 min.', 'On each side or until done (165 degrees f).', 'Remove chicken from skillet; cover to keep warm.', 'Add peppers and garlic to skillet; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Return chicken to skillet; stir in dressing.', 'Cook 2 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.']

title: Cranberry buckle
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Grease and flour 13x9-inch baking pan; set aside.', 'Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.', 'Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in cranberries.', 'Beat egg, milk and vanilla in small bowl with whisk until well blended.', 'Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.', 'Spread into prepared pan.', 'Bake 30 to 35 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.', 'Cool completely.', 'Combine all glaze ingredients in bowl.', 'Drizzle over cake.']

title: Cinnamon rolls
recipe: ['Heat oven to 375f.', 'Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar until blended.', 'Unroll dough; separate into 8 rectangles.', 'Firmly press perforations together to seal.', 'Spread with cream cheese mixture; sprinkle with cinnamon.', 'Roll up, starting at one short end; cut each into 8 slices.', 'Place, cut sides down, on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 12 to 15 min.', 'Or until golden brown.']

title: Cinnamon scones
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 425 degrees f (220 degrees c).', 'In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.', 'Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in milk just until dough clings together.', 'Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently 8 to 10 times.', 'Pat dough into a circle about 1/2 inch thick.', 'Cut into 8 wedges.', 'Place wedges on a baking sheet.', 'Brush tops with milk.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.']

title: Lemon pound cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 325f.', 'Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla.', 'Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.', 'Pour into prepared pan.', 'Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.', 'Cool completely on wire rack.', "In a small bowl, combine confectioners' sugar and lemon juice; beat until smooth.", 'Drizzle over cake.']

title: Citrus punch
recipe: ['Add water to drink mix in large plastic or glass pitcher; stir until mix is dissolved.', 'Stir in remaining ingredients.', 'Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.']

title: Chicken with caramelized onions and peppers
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chicken; cook 6 to 8 min.', 'On each side or until done (165 degrees f).', 'Remove chicken from skillet; cover to keep warm.', 'Add onions to skillet; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in peppers; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Return chicken to skillet; top with cheese.', 'Cover; cook on low heat 5 min.', 'Or until cheese is melted.']

title: Chocolate peanut butter brownies
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Line 13x9-inch pan with foil, with ends of foil extending over sides.', 'Spray with cooking spray.', 'Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted; stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Blend in eggs.', 'Stir in peanut butter.', 'Spread onto bottom of prepared pan.', 'Bake 25 to 30 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.', '(do not overbake.)', 'Cool completely.', 'Use foil handles to lift brownies from pan before cutting into bars.']

title: Orange mousse with orange cream
recipe: ['Add boiling water to gelatin mix in medium bowl; stir 2 min.', 'Until completely dissolved.', 'Stir in milk.', 'Refrigerate 1-1/2 hours or until thickened.', 'Whisk in sour cream.', 'Refrigerate 15 min.', 'Or until thickened.', 'Stir in oranges.', 'Spoon into 6-cup mold sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.', 'Unmold.']

title: Korean dipping sauce
recipe: ['In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, onion, and red pepper flakes.', 'Stir in the scallions and season with salt.']

title: Peanut butter playdough
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a food processor and pulse until smooth.', 'Serve on your favorite pasta or roll.']

title: Sauteed kale
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds.', 'Add kale and salt and pepper to taste.', 'Cook, stirring occasionally, until kale is tender, about 5 minutes.']

title: Chicken & egg salad
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.']

title: Bacon & cheese pizza
recipe: ['Heat oven to 450f.', 'Place crust on baking sheet; spread with cream cheese product.', 'Top with remaining ingredients.', 'Bake 10 to 12 min.', 'Or until mozzarella is melted and crust is golden brown.']

title: Pesto bruschetta
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Combine first 5 ingredients.', 'Spoon onto toast slices; top with cheese.', 'Bake 5 min.', 'Or until cheese is melted.']

title: Lemon vinaigrette
recipe: ['Whisk together lemon juice, vinegar, mustard, salt, and pepper in a small bowl.', 'Slowly stream in oil, whisking constantly.']

title: Spinach salad with oranges and cranberries
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.', 'Add dressing just before serving; mix lightly.']

title: Roasted red pepper and feta salad
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'Place peppers on baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.', 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Roast for 20 minutes, or until peppers are tender.', 'Remove from oven and allow to cool.', 'Once peppers are cool enough to handle, remove stems and seeds.', 'Place peppers in a large bowl.', 'Add feta cheese, onion, and feta cheese.', 'Toss to combine.', 'In a small bowl, whisk together vinegar, salt and pepper.', 'Pour over salad and toss to coat.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Fried onion rings
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 15 minutes.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Remove onions from skillet and set aside.', 'Beat eggs in a shallow dish.', 'Dip onion rings in egg, then in onion mixture.', 'Fry in hot oil until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.', 'Drain on paper towels.']

title: Curried chicken
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the onion, garlic, ginger, coriander, turmeric, salt, pepper, and cayenne.', 'Add the chicken and toss to coat.', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet.', 'Add the chicken and cook over moderately high heat, turning once, until browned, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the curry powder and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds.', 'Add the chicken and cook, stirring, until browned, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the cilantro and cook, stirring, until the chicken is cooked through, about 2 minutes longer.', 'Serve with rice.']

title: Roasted red pepper and onion soup
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Place peppers on a baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.', 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Roast for 30 minutes, or until peppers are soft.', 'Remove from oven and allow to cool.', 'Peel and chop peppers.', 'In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.', 'Add onions and garlic and saute for about 5 minutes.', 'Add peppers and saute for another 5 minutes.', 'Add roasted peppers and saute for another 5 minutes.', 'Serve hot.']

title: Grilled steak with tomato relish
recipe: ['Light a grill.', 'In a small bowl, combine the tomatoes, onion, garlic, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.', 'Grill the steak over moderately high heat, turning once, until charred and medium-rare within, about 8 minutes.', 'Transfer the steak to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes.', 'Thinly slice the steak.', 'Serve the steak with the tomato relish.']

title: Green beans with garlic
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add garlic; saute 30 seconds.', 'Add green beans; saute 2 minutes.', 'Add salt and pepper; saute 1 minute.']

title: Broccoli with olive oil
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add broccoli and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Season with salt and pepper.']

title: Creamy cheese sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.', 'Stir in milk, salt and pepper.', 'Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir in cheese until melted.']

title: Avocado salad
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the avocados, tomatoes, onion, and lime juice.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.']

title: Strawberry lemonade
recipe: ['In a large pitcher, combine the strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and water.', 'Stir until sugar is dissolved.', 'Chill until cold.']

title: Baked salmon with olive oil
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.', 'Place salmon fillets on the prepared baking sheet.', 'Drizzle olive oil over salmon fillets.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until salmon flakes easily with a fork, about 15 minutes.']

title: Cucumber & feta roll-ups
recipe: ['Mix cream cheese and feta until well blended.', 'Spread evenly onto cucumber slices; top with peppers and onions.', 'Roll up tightly.', 'Cut each roll-up into 4 slices.']

title: Santa fe grilled chicken salad
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium heat.', 'Grill chicken 6 to 8 min.', 'On each side or until done (165f), brushing occasionally with dressing.', 'Cut chicken into thin strips.', 'Combine lettuce, tomatoes, corn, onions and peppers in large bowl.', 'Add chicken and cheese; mix lightly.', 'Top tortillas with lettuce mixture and sour cream.']

title: Rosemary orange tisane
recipe: ['Place 1 rosemary sprig and 1 navel orange slice in each of 4 small teacups or heatproof glasses.', 'Pour 1 cup boiling water over each cup.']

title: Asparagus and mustard salad
recipe: ['Mix dressing and mustard in large bowl.', 'Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.', 'Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.']

title: Peach and orange compote
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.', 'Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.', 'Cool and refrigerate until ready to use.']

title: Chicken and spinach brunch bake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'Place chicken in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Top with spinach, peppers and cheese.', 'Whisk eggs and dressing until blended; pour over ingredients in dish.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until centre is set.']

title: Sun-dried tomato salsa
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions and garlic; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in tomatoes, peppers and dressing; cook 5 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.']

title: Magnolia bakery muffins
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper muffin liners.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.', 'Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.', 'Fold in the candy-coated milk chocolate pieces.', 'Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean.']

title: Ritz cracker topper
recipe: ['Cut cheese slices in half.', 'Top crackers with cheese and bacon.']

title: Blt salad
recipe: ['Toss lettuce with tomatoes, bacon and cheese in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.']

title: Bbq sauce
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan.', 'Bring to boil on medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.', 'Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 10 min., stirring occasionally.', 'Cool completely.']

title: Salsa verde shrimp & rice
recipe: ['Cook and stir onions and garlic in dressing in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add shrimp; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until shrimp turn pink.', 'Stir in salsa; simmer on medium-low heat 5 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Serve over rice.', 'Sprinkle with cheese.']

title: Roasted red pepper and onion dip
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a large bowl, toss together the red peppers, onion, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper.', 'Spread the mixture on the baking sheet in an even layer.', 'Roast for 20 minutes, stirring once halfway through.', 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool.', 'Serve with crudites or crackers.']

title: Coconut cream cheese cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease and flour a 9x13 inch pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the coconut and salt.', 'Mix in the self-rising flour and mix until just incorporated.', 'Pour batter into the prepared pan.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.', 'Allow to cool in the pan for 10 minutes before inverting onto a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Apple butter
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the apples, water, raisins, sugar and cinnamon.', 'Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.', 'Stir in butter and serve warm or at room temperature.']

title: Chocolate peanut butter cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.', 'Add the flour and salt and mix until combined.', 'Roll dough into 1 inch balls and place on a parchment lined baking sheet.', 'Bake for 10-12 minutes.', 'Remove from the oven and let cool on a wire rack.', 'Melt chocolate in a double boiler or in the microwave.', 'Dip each cookie into the chocolate and place on a cooling rack.', 'Let cool completely.']

title: Cinnamon chicken
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400f.', 'Mix sugar and cinnamon in shallow dish.', 'Add chicken; turn to evenly coat both sides of each breast.', 'Place in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 30 min.', 'Or until chicken is done (165 degrees f).', 'Meanwhile, melt butter in small saucepan on medium heat.', 'Add nuts; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or until nuts are lightly toasted.', 'Serve chicken topped with the sauce.']

title: Bacon-ranch dip
recipe: ['Mix ingredients until blended.', 'Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.']

title: Spinach and corn saute
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add garlic; cook and stir 1 min.', 'Add spinach, corn and pepper; cook and stir 3 to 5 min.', 'Or until spinach is wilted.']

title: Carrot dumplings
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the carrots, onion, flour, baking powder and salt.', 'In a small bowl, combine the egg and water.', 'Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened.', 'Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.', 'Bake at 400 degrees f for 20 minutes or until golden brown.', 'Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine the butter and water.', 'Bring to a boil.', 'Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.', 'Stir in the carrots.', 'Serve with the dumplings.']

title: Chocolate eclair cake
recipe: ['Beat pudding mix, milk and eggs in large bowl with whisk 2 min.', 'Stir in cool whip.', 'Layer half each of the grahams, pudding mixture and chocolate in 13x9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray; repeat layers.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.', 'Microwave chocolate and butter in microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted; stir until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is well blended.', 'Drizzle over dessert.']

title: Spinach and feta frittata
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Beat eggs and pepper in medium bowl with whisk until blended.', 'Add spinach, feta and 1/4 cup parmesan; mix well.', 'Pour into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 25 min.', 'Or until center is set.', 'Sprinkle with remaining parmesan.', 'Bake 5 min.', 'Or until melted.']

title: Jell-o fruit cups
recipe: ['Stir boiling water into dry gelatin mix in medium bowl at least 2 min.', 'Until completely dissolved.', 'Stir in cold water.', 'Pour into 12 (5-oz.)', 'Paper or plastic cups.', 'Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.', 'Unmold.', 'Store leftover desserts in refrigerator.']

title: Cheesy peas
recipe: ['Cook peas as directed on package.', 'Stir in cheese.']

title: Chicken cacciatore
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chicken; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until done.', 'Add peppers; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in pasta sauce; cook 5 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Top with cheese.']

title: Roasted acorn squash
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds and membranes.', 'Place squash halves, cut sides down, on a foil-lined baking sheet.', 'Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Roast for 30 minutes.', 'Meanwhile, melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Add squash and cook, stirring occasionally, until squash is tender, about 10 minutes.']

title: Easy peanut butter pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a medium bowl, mix together the peanut butter, sugar, flour, and salt.', 'Stir in the milk until smooth.', 'Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.']

title: Raspberry coconut milk
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the coconut milk, water, sugar and raspberries.', 'Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.', 'Reduce the heat to moderately low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the raspberries are very soft, about 20 minutes.', 'Strain the syrup through a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing on the solids.', 'Discard the solids.', 'Serve the strained milk in bowls.']

title: Banana bread
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Grease and flour a 9x5 loaf pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.', 'Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Stir in bananas and vanilla.', 'In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.', 'Add to creamed mixture alternately with the dry ingredients, mixing just until combined.', 'Pour into prepared pan.', 'Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Lemon pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the lemon juice and vanilla.', 'Combine the flour and salt; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.', 'Pour into the prepared pie crust.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.', 'Cool on a wire rack.']
